</paragraph>
<paragraph id="64725C122B10694081F817DF12F6AB30" blockId="1.[706,1194,1469,1730]" pageId="1">
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B10694081F817DF122DA890" author="Dejean &amp; Catalogue des Coleopteres de la Collection" box="[730,881,1469,1490]" pageId="1" refId="ref4206" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. 1835. Catalogue des Coleopteres de la Collection de M. le Comte Dejean. [Livraison 4]. Mequignon-Marvis, Paris, France." type="journal volume" year="1835">Dejean (1835)</bibRefCitation>
listed the genus 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B106940871117DF1524A890" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1835" box="[1075,1144,1469,1490]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B106940871117DF1524A890" box="[1075,1144,1469,1490]" italics="true" pageId="1">Aphies</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and included three species not described: 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B106940870217BA1258AB45" authority="Dejean" authorityName="sensu Dejean" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythrodera">
<emphasis id="56B980002B106940870217BA15F4A8AF" box="[1056,1192,1496,1517]" italics="true" pageId="1">A. erythrodera</emphasis>
Dejean
</taxonomicName>
from “Carthagena”; 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B10694080ED1790152FAB45" authority="Dejean" authorityName="&quot; sensu Dejean" authorityYear="1835" box="[975,1139,1522,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lebasii">
<emphasis id="56B980002B10694080ED17901575AB45" box="[975,1065,1522,1543]" italics="true" pageId="1">A. lebasii</emphasis>
Dejean
</taxonomicName>
from “Carthagena”; and 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B106940805A146F1560AB60" authority="Dejean" authorityName="Dejean" box="[888,1084,1549,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis id="56B980002B106940805A146F12AEAB60" box="[888,1010,1549,1570]" italics="true" pageId="1">A. peruviana</emphasis>
Dejean
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="1CDA1C822B106940875A146F15FAAB60" box="[1144,1190,1549,1570]" name="Peru" pageId="1">Peru</collectingCountry>
. Bousquet and Bouchard (2013) correctly pointed out: “ 
<emphasis id="56B980002B10694081D4142012ADAB15" bold="true" box="[758,1009,1602,1623]" pageId="1">
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B10694081D4142012B1AB15" authority="Dejean, 1835: 353" authorityName="Dejean" authorityPageNumber="353" authorityYear="1835" box="[758,1005,1602,1623]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B10694081D41420126BAB15" bold="true" box="[758,823,1602,1623]" italics="true" pageId="1">Aphies</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B106940801F142012B1AB15" author="Dejean &amp; Catalogue des Coleopteres de la Collection" box="[829,1005,1602,1623]" pageId="1" refId="ref4206" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. 1835. Catalogue des Coleopteres de la Collection de M. le Comte Dejean. [Livraison 4]. Mequignon-Marvis, Paris, France." type="journal volume" year="1835">Dejean, 1835: 353</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Originally included available species: none.”
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2CD70F992B10694381F8141510C5A871" lastPageId="2" pageId="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="64725C122B10694081F8141515F4AB83" blockId="1.[706,1194,1469,1730]" pageId="1">
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B10694081F814151228ABCE" author="Thomson" box="[730,884,1655,1676]" pageId="1" pagination="291 - 320" refId="ref4551" refString="Thomson, J. 1857. Description de cerambycides nouveaux ou peu connus de ma collection. Archives Entomologiques 1: 291 - 320." type="journal article" year="1857">Thomson (1857)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B10694080F51415156CABCE" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1857" box="[983,1072,1655,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B10694080F51415156CABCE" box="[983,1072,1655,1676]" italics="true" pageId="1">Amillarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and reported “ 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B10694081EE14F01239ABE5" authority="Dej. Cat." authorityName="Dej. Cat." box="[716,869,1682,1703]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B10694081EE14F01256ABE5" box="[716,778,1682,1703]" italics="true" pageId="1">Aphies</emphasis>
Dej. Cat.
</taxonomicName>
3 
<superScript id="93B8F15A2B106940805714EE1221ABD8" attach="left" box="[885,893,1676,1690]" fontSize="6" pageId="1">e</superScript>
édit. p. 379, nom déjà employé: 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B10694081E014CE13ABAB83" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1748" box="[706,759,1708,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B10694081E014CE13ABAB83" box="[706,759,1708,1729]" italics="true" pageId="1">Aphis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Linné Syst. Nat. 1748 Hemiptères.” There is
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="64725C122B10694081B9148413E7ABBB" blockId="1.[667,699,1766,1785]" box="[667,699,1766,1785]" pageId="1">805</paragraph>
<paragraph id="64725C122B13694383B512A0101FAEC8" blockId="2.[151,639,194,1729]" pageId="2">
more than one mistake in this statement. 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943813712A0130FAD95" box="[533,595,194,215]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943813712A0130FAD95" box="[533,595,194,215]" italics="true" pageId="2">Aphies</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not listed for the first time in the third Dejean catalogue, but in the second catalogue on page 353. 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694383B513701041AC65" authority="Dejean" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1835" box="[151,285,274,295]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694383B513701189AC65" box="[151,213,274,295]" italics="true" pageId="2">Aphies</emphasis>
Dejean
</taxonomicName>
is not a homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694382C81370119BAC03" authority="Linnaeus, 1748" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1748" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694382C813701342AC65" box="[490,542,274,295]" italics="true" pageId="2">Aphis</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 1748
</taxonomicName>
, because even in 1857 zoologists did not accept works published before the 12 
<superScript id="93B8F15A2B13694382E013201093AC12" attach="left" box="[450,463,322,336]" fontSize="6" pageId="2">th</superScript>
edition [currently 10 
<superScript id="93B8F15A2B136943838C133E11E7AC28" attach="left" box="[174,187,348,362]" fontSize="6" pageId="2">th</superScript>
edition] of the “Systema Naturae” (
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B136943813D130011A2ACD3" author="Strickland" pageId="2" pagination="259 - 275" refId="ref4436" refString="Strickland, H. E., W. J. Philips, J. Richardson, R. Owen, L. Jenyns, W. J. Broderip, J. S. Henslow, W. E. Shuckars, G. R. Waterhouse, W. Yarrell, C. Darwin, and J. O. Westwood. 1843. Series of propositions for rendering the nomenclature of zoology uniform and permanent, being the report of a committee for the consideration of the subject appointed by the British Association for the Advancement of Science. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History 11: 259 - 275." type="journal article" year="1843">
Strickland 
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694383B5131E119BACD3" box="[151,199,380,401]" italics="true" pageId="2">et al.</emphasis>
1843
</bibRefCitation>
), which is the work was widely accepted and is the base of the current International Code of Zoological Nomenclature). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B136943810313D3104DACA3" author="Strickland" pageId="2" pagination="259 - 275" refId="ref4436" refString="Strickland, H. E., W. J. Philips, J. Richardson, R. Owen, L. Jenyns, W. J. Broderip, J. S. Henslow, W. E. Shuckars, G. R. Waterhouse, W. Yarrell, C. Darwin, and J. O. Westwood. 1843. Series of propositions for rendering the nomenclature of zoology uniform and permanent, being the report of a committee for the consideration of the subject appointed by the British Association for the Advancement of Science. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History 11: 259 - 275." type="journal article" year="1843">
Strickland 
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694383B513AE1196ACA3" box="[151,202,460,481]" italics="true" pageId="2">et al.</emphasis>
(1843)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943823C13AE10FBACA3" authority="Dejean" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1835" box="[286,423,460,481]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943823C13AE1000ACA3" box="[286,348,460,481]" italics="true" pageId="2">Aphies</emphasis>
Dejean
</taxonomicName>
is not a homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694383BA13841051ACB9" authority="Linne" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1748" box="[152,269,486,507]" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694383BA13841190ACB9" box="[152,204,486,507]" italics="true" pageId="2">Aphis</emphasis>
Linné
</taxonomicName>
because they are not identical. Also according to 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B136943823D10631351AF54" author="Strickland" box="[287,525,513,534]" pageId="2" pagination="259 - 275" refId="ref4436" refString="Strickland, H. E., W. J. Philips, J. Richardson, R. Owen, L. Jenyns, W. J. Broderip, J. S. Henslow, W. E. Shuckars, G. R. Waterhouse, W. Yarrell, C. Darwin, and J. O. Westwood. 1843. Series of propositions for rendering the nomenclature of zoology uniform and permanent, being the report of a committee for the consideration of the subject appointed by the British Association for the Advancement of Science. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History 11: 259 - 275." type="journal article" year="1843">
Strickland 
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694382A81063109EAF54" box="[394,450,513,534]" italics="true" pageId="2">et al.</emphasis>
(1843)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943813D10631301AF54" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1835" box="[543,605,513,534]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943813D10631301AF54" box="[543,605,513,534]" italics="true" pageId="2">Aphies</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B13694383BA10791043AF72" author="Dejean &amp; Catalogue des Coleopteres de la Collection" box="[152,287,539,560]" pageId="2" refId="ref4206" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. 1835. Catalogue des Coleopteres de la Collection de M. le Comte Dejean. [Livraison 4]. Mequignon-Marvis, Paris, France." type="journal volume" year="1835">Dejean (1835)</bibRefCitation>
is not available. Although 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B136943810410791189AF09" author="Thomson" pageId="2" pagination="291 - 320" refId="ref4551" refString="Thomson, J. 1857. Description de cerambycides nouveaux ou peu connus de ma collection. Archives Entomologiques 1: 291 - 320." type="journal article" year="1857">Thomson (1857)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943821E105410C9AF09" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1857" box="[316,405,566,587]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943821E105410C9AF09" box="[316,405,566,587]" italics="true" pageId="2">Amillarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, he did not describe the species included in this genus, merely mentioning: “ 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B1369438383100910CEAFC2" authority="Guerin" authorityName="Guerin" box="[161,402,619,640]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943838310091017AFC2" box="[161,331,619,640]" italics="true" pageId="2">Amillarus apicalis</emphasis>
Guérin
</taxonomicName>
?” Unfortunately, it was not possible to know if he was referring to a species described or mentioned by Guérin-Méneville. 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B13694383BA10D9101CAF92" author="Thomson" box="[152,320,699,720]" pageId="2" pagination="129 - 396" refId="ref4576" refString="Thomson, J. 1860 - 61. Essai d' une classification de la famille des cerambycides et materiaux pour servir a une monographie de cette famille. Paris, France. 396 pp. + 3 pls. [1860: pp. xvi + 128; 1861: pp. 129 - 396]." type="book chapter" year="1860">Thomson (1860)</bibRefCitation>
also recorded “ 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694382D710D911A1AFA8" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">AMILLARUS APICALIS</taxonomicName>
(Guérin M. S. S.?). Thomson.” According to 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B13694383911092100CAE47" author="Marinoni" box="[179,336,752,773]" pageId="2" pagination="37 - 55" refId="ref4367" refString="Marinoni, R. C. 1977. Some genera of Lamiinae and their type-species (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Dusenia 10 (1): 37 - 55." type="journal article" year="1977">Marinoni (1977)</bibRefCitation>
, “Thomson described the genus 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694383BA116811B1AE5D" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1857" box="[152,237,778,799]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694383BA116811B1AE5D" box="[152,237,778,799]" italics="true" pageId="2">Amillarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and quoted the species “ 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694382E411681338AE5D" authority="Guerin" authorityName="Guerin" box="[454,612,778,799]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694382E41168137EAE5D" box="[454,546,778,799]" italics="true" pageId="2">A. apicalis</emphasis>
Guérin
</taxonomicName>
?” The description of the genus applies to the species, heretofore undescribed.” 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B13694382BA1122134AAE17" author="ICZN &amp; International Code of Zoological Nomenclature" box="[408,534,832,853]" pageId="2" refId="ref4305" refString="ICZN. 1964. International Code of Zoological Nomenclature adopted by the XV International Congress of Zoology. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, UK." type="book" year="1964">ICZN (1964</bibRefCitation>
[code in force in 1977], 1999) allow considering 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943813B11381321AE2D" box="[537,637,858,879]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943813B11381321AE2D" box="[537,637,858,879]" italics="true" pageId="2">A. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="64725C122B136943838D11ED10D2A906" blockId="2.[151,639,194,1729]" pageId="2">
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B136943838D11ED103FAEE6" author="Aurivillius" box="[175,355,911,932]" pageId="2" pagination="405 - 436" refId="ref3785" refString="Aurivillius, C. 1922. Neue oder wenig bekannte Coleoptera Longicornia. 18. Arkiv for Zoologi 14 (18): 405 - 436." type="journal article" year="1922">Aurivillius (1922)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694382FB11ED1301AEE6" authorityName="Mahunka" authorityYear="1984" box="[473,605,911,932]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Didymonycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694382FB11ED1301AEE6" box="[473,605,911,932]" italics="true" pageId="2">Didymonycha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to include his new species, 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694382A911C81326AEFD" authority="Aurivillius" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1922" box="[395,634,938,959]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singularis">
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694382A911C81355AEFD" box="[395,521,938,959]" italics="true" pageId="2">D. singularis</emphasis>
Aurivillius
</taxonomicName>
, and placed the genus in a new tribe 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694382CA11A61327AE9B" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1922" box="[488,635,964,985]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Didymonychini">Didymonychini</taxonomicName>
. Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B13694383FB11BD10D8AEB6" author="Aurivillius" box="[217,388,991,1012]" pageId="2" pagination="503 - 524" refId="ref3812" refString="Aurivillius, C. 1925. Neue oder wenig bekannte Coleoptera Longicornia. 21. Arkiv for Zoologi 18 A (9): 503 - 524." type="journal article" year="1925">Aurivillius (1925)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694382DC11BD1322AEB6" authorityName="Mahunka" authorityYear="1984" box="[510,638,991,1012]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Didymonycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694382DC11BD1322AEB6" box="[510,638,991,1012]" italics="true" pageId="2">Didymonycha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as different from 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943826E119810F9A94D" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1857" box="[332,421,1018,1039]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943826E119810F9A94D" box="[332,421,1018,1039]" italics="true" pageId="2">Amillarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because he wrongly interpreted the claws in 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943825016761088A96B" box="[370,468,1044,1065]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943825016761088A96B" box="[370,468,1044,1065]" italics="true" pageId="2">A. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, considering them as not fused at their base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="64725C122B136943838D162B10C5A871" blockId="2.[151,639,194,1729]" pageId="2">
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B136943838D162B1009A91C" author="Breuning" box="[175,341,1097,1118]" pageId="2" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref3997" refString="Breuning, S. 1948. Nouvelles formes de Lamiaires (Deuxieme partie). Bulletin du Museum d' Histoire Naturelle de Belgique 24 (47): 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="1948">Breuning (1948)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694382E9162B1321A91C" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1948" box="[459,637,1097,1118]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichogrammopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694382E9162B1321A91C" box="[459,637,1097,1118]" italics="true" pageId="2">Trichogrammopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for a single species from 
<collectingCountry id="1CDA1C822B136943828A160610A5A93B" box="[424,505,1124,1145]" name="Ecuador" pageId="2">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943812816061064A9D6" authority="Breuning, 1948" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1948" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichogrammopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficollis">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943812816061321A93B" box="[522,637,1124,1145]" italics="true" pageId="2">T. ruficollis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B13694383BA161D1064A9D6" author="Breuning" box="[152,312,1151,1172]" pageId="2" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref3997" refString="Breuning, S. 1948. Nouvelles formes de Lamiaires (Deuxieme partie). Bulletin du Museum d' Histoire Naturelle de Belgique 24 (47): 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="1948">Breuning, 1948</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B136943826B161D10ACA9D6" author="Breuning &amp; Catalogue des Lamiaires du Monde" box="[329,496,1151,1172]" pageId="2" pagination="183 - 284" refId="ref4029" refString="Breuning, S. 1961. Catalogue des Lamiaires du Monde (Col., Cerambycidae). 4 Lief. Museum G. Frey, Tutzing bei Munchen, p. 183 - 284." type="book chapter" year="1961">Breuning (1961)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694383BA16FB100DA9EC" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1948" box="[152,337,1177,1198]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Trichogrammopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694383BA16FB100DA9EC" box="[152,337,1177,1198]" italics="true" pageId="2">Trichogrammopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943829316FB1366A9EC" authorityName="Mahunka" authorityYear="1984" box="[433,570,1177,1198]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Didymonycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943829316FB1366A9EC" box="[433,570,1177,1198]" italics="true" pageId="2">Didymonycha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B13694383BA16D6101CA98B" author="Breuning &amp; Revision des Agapanthiini Muls" box="[152,320,1204,1225]" pageId="2" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref4065" refString="Breuning, S. 1962. Revision des Agapanthiini Muls. americains (Col., Cerambycidae). Pesquisas (6) 13: 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1962">Breuning (1962)</bibRefCitation>
considered both as synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943839616AC1049A9A1" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1857" box="[180,277,1230,1251]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943839616AC1049A9A1" box="[180,277,1230,1251]" italics="true" pageId="2">Amillarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. After examining photographs and/ or specimens of the 
<typeStatus id="BB76E2B02B1369438249168B10C9A9BC" box="[363,405,1257,1278]" pageId="2">type</typeStatus>
species of each genus involved, we agree with the synonymies proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B1369438395177C1013A871" author="Breuning &amp; Catalogue des Lamiaires du Monde" box="[183,335,1310,1331]" pageId="2" pagination="183 - 284" refId="ref4029" refString="Breuning, S. 1961. Catalogue des Lamiaires du Monde (Col., Cerambycidae). 4 Lief. Museum G. Frey, Tutzing bei Munchen, p. 183 - 284." type="book chapter" year="1961">Breuning (1961</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B1369438279177C10D2A871" author="Breuning &amp; Revision des Agapanthiini Muls" box="[347,398,1310,1331]" pageId="2" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref4065" refString="Breuning, S. 1962. Revision des Agapanthiini Muls. americains (Col., Cerambycidae). Pesquisas (6) 13: 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1962">1962</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2CD70F992B136943838D175A150CADB0" pageId="2" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="64725C122B136943838D175A150CADB0" blockId="2.[151,639,194,1729]" lastBlockId="2.[685,1171,194,242]" pageId="2">
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943838D175A11B3A80F" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1835" box="[175,239,1336,1357]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943838D175A11B3A80F" box="[175,239,1336,1357]" italics="true" pageId="2">Aphies</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered available by 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B1369438102175A118BA82A" author="Chevrolat" pageId="2" pagination="185 - 192" refId="ref4165" refString="Chevrolat, L. A. 1861. Reflexions et notes synonymiques sur le travail de M. James Thomson sur les Cerambycides, avec descriptions de quelques nouvelles especes. The Journal of Entomology 1: 185 - 192." type="journal article" year="1861">Chevrolat (1861)</bibRefCitation>
(
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B13694383C91731102DA82A" author="Monne" box="[235,369,1363,1384]" pageId="2" refId="ref4398" refString="Monne, M. A. 2016. Catalogue of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of the Neotropical Region. Part II. Subfamily Cerambycinae. www. cerambyxcat. com / (accessed April 2016)." type="journal volume" year="2016">Monné 2016</bibRefCitation>
). However, we think that there is no doubt that 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B1369438259170C137EA8C1" author="Chevrolat" box="[379,546,1390,1411]" pageId="2" pagination="185 - 192" refId="ref4165" refString="Chevrolat, L. A. 1861. Reflexions et notes synonymiques sur le travail de M. James Thomson sur les Cerambycides, avec descriptions de quelques nouvelles especes. The Journal of Entomology 1: 185 - 192." type="journal article" year="1861">Chevrolat (1861)</bibRefCitation>
was just mentioning the species (
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943825C17EA135BA8DF" authorityName="sensu Dejean" authorityYear="1835" box="[382,519,1416,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythrodera">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943825C17EA135BA8DF" box="[382,519,1416,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2">A. erythrodera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B136943839B17C11019A8FA" author="Dejean &amp; Catalogue des Coleopteres de la Collection" box="[185,325,1443,1464]" pageId="2" refId="ref4206" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. 1835. Catalogue des Coleopteres de la Collection de M. le Comte Dejean. [Livraison 4]. Mequignon-Marvis, Paris, France." type="journal volume" year="1835">Dejean (1835)</bibRefCitation>
: “ 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943827F17C11326A8FA" authority=", Th., 1860" authorityName="Th." authorityYear="1860" box="[349,634,1443,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943827F17C11355A8FA" box="[349,521,1443,1464]" italics="true" pageId="2">Amillarus apicalis</emphasis>
, Th., 1860
</taxonomicName>
. Syn. 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694383EA17DF10ECA890" authority="Lebasii, Dej. Cat." authorityName="Lebasii, Dej. Cat." box="[200,432,1469,1490]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694383EA17DF100CA890" box="[200,336,1469,1490]" italics="true" pageId="2">Aphies Lebasii</emphasis>
, Dej. Cat.
</taxonomicName>
iii. p. 379. – 
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943810E17DF1363A891" box="[556,575,1469,1491]" italics="true" pageId="2">L’</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943811D17DF1067A8AF" authority=", Dej." authorityName="Dej." class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythrodera">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943811D17DF1059A8AF" italics="true" pageId="2">Aphies erythrodera</emphasis>
, Dej.
</taxonomicName>
, que M. Thomson y raporte come variété, me parait être distincte.” Consequently, 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694383BA146F1079AB60" authority="Dejean" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1835" box="[152,293,1549,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694383BA146F118AAB60" box="[152,214,1549,1570]" italics="true" pageId="2">Aphies</emphasis>
Dejean
</taxonomicName>
is not an available genus name. Notwithstanding, 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943826714451379AB7E" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1861" box="[325,549,1575,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythroderus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943826714451379AB7E" box="[325,549,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="2">Amillarus erythroderus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[species group name changed accordingly to gender of the genus] is available in 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B1369438253143F134AAB30" author="Chevrolat" box="[369,534,1629,1650]" pageId="2" pagination="185 - 192" refId="ref4165" refString="Chevrolat, L. A. 1861. Reflexions et notes synonymiques sur le travail de M. James Thomson sur les Cerambycides, avec descriptions de quelques nouvelles especes. The Journal of Entomology 1: 185 - 192." type="journal article" year="1861">Chevrolat (1861)</bibRefCitation>
. Thus, the correct citation of the species is 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943829314151076ABE5" authority="Chevrolat, 1861" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1861" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythroderus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943829314151322ABCE" box="[433,638,1655,1676]" italics="true" pageId="2">Amillarus erythroderus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B13694383B514F01076ABE5" author="Chevrolat" box="[151,298,1682,1703]" pageId="2" pagination="185 - 192" refId="ref4165" refString="Chevrolat, L. A. 1861. Reflexions et notes synonymiques sur le travail de M. James Thomson sur les Cerambycides, avec descriptions de quelques nouvelles especes. The Journal of Entomology 1: 185 - 192." type="journal article" year="1861">Chevrolat, 1861</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and not 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694382A614F01192AB83" authority="(Chevrolat, 1861)" baseAuthorityName="Chevrolat" baseAuthorityYear="1861" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythroderus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694382A614F0134EABE5" box="[388,530,1682,1703]" italics="true" pageId="2">A. erythroderus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B136943810314F0119AAB83" author="Chevrolat" pageId="2" pagination="185 - 192" refId="ref4165" refString="Chevrolat, L. A. 1861. Reflexions et notes synonymiques sur le travail de M. James Thomson sur les Cerambycides, avec descriptions de quelques nouvelles especes. The Journal of Entomology 1: 185 - 192." type="journal article" year="1861">Chevrolat, 1861</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. From what is possible to see, 
<bibRefCitation id="005C21E32B136943813B14CE13B0AD95" author="Aurivillius" box="[537,748,194,1729]" pageId="2" pagination="405 - 436" refId="ref3785" refString="Aurivillius, C. 1922. Neue oder wenig bekannte Coleoptera Longicornia. 18. Arkiv for Zoologi 14 (18): 405 - 436." type="journal article" year="1922">Aurivillius (1922)</bibRefCitation>
also agreed with this, because 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B136943870712A01538AD95" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1835" box="[1061,1124,194,215]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aphies" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B136943870712A01538AD95" box="[1061,1124,194,215]" italics="true" pageId="2">Aphies</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not mentioned in the synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="A3CD27912B13694380CD12BF1516ADB0" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1857" box="[1007,1098,221,242]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amillarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="56B980002B13694380CD12BF1516ADB0" box="[1007,1098,221,242]" italics="true" pageId="2">Amillarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
